 <name>rdump</name>
 <channel>pecl.php.net</channel>
 <summary>Capture a PHP process's own memory for offline analysis with reli (finding leaks, reference cycles, memory bottlenecks, etc.).</summary>
 <description>
ext-rdump writes a snapshot of the current PHP process's own memory to a
file, in the RDUMP format used by reli (reliforp/reli-prof). The dump is
analysed offline with reli to inspect the call stack and per-object memory
usage and to find memory leaks, reference cycles and bottlenecks. The
snapshot is taken from inside the process, so no ptrace is required.
Linux only; PHP 7.0+, NTS and ZTS.
 </description>
